@UTF8
@Begin
@Languages:	eng
@Participants:	INV Investigator
@ID:	eng|corpus|INV|||||Investigator|||
@Comment:	Event segment (&=...) bodies that contain `^`, `{`, `}`, or `$` —
@Comment:	all four are allowed inside event_segment per grammar.js's
@Comment:	EVENT_SEGMENT_FORBIDDEN (none of them appear in the forbidden
@Comment:	set). One wild-corpus example exists in shaddend.cha as
@Comment:	`&=reads:boardLas^_Palmas`. The re2c lexer's `ev_char` was
@Comment:	over-restrictive (forbade all four), splitting otherwise-whole
@Comment:	events into separate event + word tokens. Found by the re2c
@Comment:	parity oracle on 2026-04-30; lexer aligned to grammar.js.
*INV:	+< &=reads:boardLas^_Palmas .
*INV:	&=points^upward yes .
*INV:	&=foo{bar} ok .
*INV:	&=baz}qux ok .
*INV:	&=name$suffix done .
@End
